        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-2">What is the rated capacity of the Alfa Laval NX 418 decanter centrifuge?</h3>
            <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">The Alfa Laval NX 418 B31-G two-phase decanter centrifuge has a rated capacity of 110 GPM on water sludge thickening. The three-phase UVNX 418 variant has a rated capacity of 70 GPM on fish stickwater and fishmeal separation.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-2">What is the difference between the NX 418 and UVNX 418 decanter centrifuges?</h3>
            <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">The NX 418 is a two-phase decanter centrifuge designed for liquid-solid separation such as sludge thickening and dewatering. The UVNX 418 is a three-phase decanter (tricanter) designed for liquid-liquid-solid separation applications such as fish oil, olive oil, and animal fat rendering.</p>
